@dmitry-prokopchenkov This sounds like a pretty good plan. I like the idea of storing the trace context (basically just `ZipkinLoggingContext`) to thread local. I think you meant non-inheritable trace contexts in brave, but yeah this sounds exactly like that. 

I would not get rid of the log handler stuff entirely, though. It is sometimes nice to be able to just say `zipkin_logger.debug(some_dict_form_of_span)`. We've seen a few cases of people using py_zipkin this way. I think it would be enough to make the log handler a singleton that logs to the thread local trace context (so in `emit` instead of `self.store_local_span()` it would be `thread_local_trace_context().store_local_span()`).

If you want to take a stab at this, feel free! Let me know if you need any help with it.

