Hi @daveFNbuck 

Ok, here a starting point:

```python
import luigi

class FinalTask(luigi.Task):
    def requires(self):
        return []

class A(luigi.Task):
    def requires(self):
        yield FinalTask()

class B(luigi.Task):
    def requires(self):
        yield FinalTask()

class Recursive(luigi.Task):
    param = luigi.IntParameter()

    def requires(self):
        if self.param:
            yield Recursive(param=self.param - 1)
        else:
            yield FinalTask()

class Range(luigi.Task):
    def requires(self):
        for i in range(2):
            yield Recursive(param=i)
```

This is how you do it:

    python -m luigi --module hello Range && python -m luigi --module hello A

Then check out the *reverse* dependency graph of `FinalTask`

![selection_089](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/294349/10399064/ccedee50-6eb0-11e5-8053-3ce5bd19b6aa.png)

