Thank you @NikolajBjorner . I made it work with the following code:
```
	z3::context ctx;
	z3::solver solver(ctx);

	char *formula1 = "(assert (and (= SymVar_0 (_ bv4 32)) (= SymVar_1 (_ bv8 32))))";

	Z3_symbol symbols[2];
	z3::symbol symbol1 = ctx.str_symbol("SymVar_0");
	symbols[0] = symbol1.operator Z3_symbol();
	z3::symbol symbol2 = ctx.str_symbol("SymVar_1");
	symbols[1] = symbol2.operator Z3_symbol();

	Z3_func_decl decl_list[2];
	Z3_sort bv_sort_32 = Z3_mk_bv_sort(ctx, 32);
	z3::sort_vector sort_v(ctx);
	z3::func_decl fun1 = ctx.function(symbol1, sort_v, ctx.bv_sort(32));
	decl_list[0] = fun1.operator Z3_func_decl();
	z3::func_decl fun2 = ctx.function(symbol2, sort_v, ctx.bv_sort(32));
	decl_list[1] = fun2.operator Z3_func_decl();

	Z3_ast ast = Z3_parse_smtlib2_string(ctx, (Z3_string)formula1, 0, 0, 0, 2, symbols, decl_list);
	z3::expr eq2(ctx, ast);
	solver.add(eq2);
	if (solver.check() == z3::sat)
	{
		printf("Solved\n");
	}
```

@franknitty69 The version of DK on Solo is 1.1 - which pre-dates addition of the code to get the battery information. If you need to get this information, you can always using the mavlink message handler and capture the value yourself. There is an example of how to do this in [this pull request](https://github.com/dronekit/dronekit-python/pull/287/files) (not on live docs yet, but you can read the source). 

At the moment there is no supported path for updating the version of DK on Solo. This is a known issue, and is being worked on. I can't give you an ETA, but I suspect we're looking at months not days for the next update.

I'm therefore closing this issue.

